The paper presents a framework for modeling, planning, and controlling legged microrobots, which falls under the scope of robotics (cs.RO). The authors use a variational contact-implicit trajectory optimization method, which involves optimization and control theory (cs.SY). The paper also involves computer vision techniques for analyzing the robot's motion (cs.CV) and mechanical engineering principles for designing the microrobot (cs.ME). Finally, the paper specifically focuses on legged robots, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.ROBOTS).
